{"key":"post-11005212","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11005212</id>\n<content>5500 K is fine.&amp;nbsp; If you buy another one in the future, 6500 K is a bit better, but don't toss out your 5.5K CFL.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Condensation on top of a bulk substrate is normal.&amp;nbsp; It doesn't cause hollow stems.&amp;nbsp; The most likely cause of that is growing at high temperature.&amp;nbsp; Hollow stems are a sign of very rapid growth, and higher temps can stimulate rapid growth.&amp;nbsp; Fruit quality is better if you'll grow at normal room temp.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;It's best not to disturb your bulk substrate. There's nothing to be gained by cutting away part of it.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11005849</next>\n<prev>11004351</prev>\n<first>10963940</first>\n<last>11018725</last>\n<when>1252190712</when>\n<utime>09/06/09 01:45 AM</utime>\n</post>"}